    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oleaginous liquid derived from coal tar that is widely used as a wood preservative because it is toxic to wood-destroying organisms. It is commonly applied to utility poles or pilings. It is dark in color and has a characteristic odor. Wood treated with coal tar creosote cannot be painted, and is not used in interior applications or on finished lumber.</Note_Text>
